				<h3 id="post-3080"><a href="http://tradewithdave.com/?p=3080" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Missing Presidential Blog Post Questioned">Missing Presidential Blog Post Questioned</a></h3>
				<small>Thursday, October 28th, 2010</small>

				<div class="entry">
					<div style="float: right; margin-left: 10px;"><a href="https://twitter.com/share" class="twitter-share-button" data-via="tradewithdave" data-count="vertical" data-url="http://tradewithdave.com/?p=3080">Tweet</a></div>
<p>Like Stephen Colbert and John Stewart, in our own small way the folks here at TradeWithDave want to contribute to the effort to restore sanity. This is the spot where we had been planning to post the video intereview of President Obama on Comedy Central&#8217;s <em>Jon Stewart&#8217;s ~ The Daily Show.  </em>On second thought we decided not to post the video because from what we can see it only restores one thing &#8211; Viacom&#8217;s stock price through advertising revenue.  Instead we thought we would simply post this video of the man who will make money off of everyone who attends the rally and watches the shows. </p>
<p>Here is a link to a video from the tv show <em>The View</em> reportedly of a voice mail from the CEO of Viacom/MTV Networks/Comedy Networks/Comedy Central, Mr. Sumner Redstone.  Mr. Redstone makes it very clear that he is not trying to keep fear alive and that he does not intend to kill anyone.</p>
